The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Centurion Bank of Punjab has launched a priority banking service, Centurion Elite. Customers will have to maintain a minimum deposit of Rs 10 lakh but they can start by opening a savings account with a minimum of Rs 1 lakh under this scheme. For every 150 to 250 customers, there will be a dedicated relationship manager to assist and guide in effective wealth management. Other services include one-point access to investment and stock broking services, doorstep banking and expert advice on all financial needs as well as enhanced withdrawal limit of Rs 1 lakh a day.

 Punjab National Bank has reduced the interest rate on its education loan by 125 basis points with effect from April this year. The bank is now charging an interest rate of 11.5 per cent per annum for loans up to Rs 4 lakh under its Vidya Lakshay Puri scheme and 10.5 per cent per annum under its Sarvottam Siksha scheme. 

 DBS Chola Mutual Fund has announced April 12 as the record date for receiving the payout under the dividend option of its Fixed Maturity Plan Series 6 Quarterly II. The company plans to distribute the entire appreciation in the net asset value between January 12 and April 12 as dividend to unit holders. 




